# Global Claude Code Instructions

This file applies to all Claude Code sessions on this machine ({{ .machine_name }}, profile: {{ last .profiles }}).

## Response Style

- Lead with the answer — skip preamble and summaries
- Concise over verbose; one sentence beats three
- No emojis unless explicitly requested
- No docstrings or comments on code I didn't change

## Git

- Never add `Co-Authored-By` trailers to commit messages
- Create new commits rather than amending (unless explicitly asked)
- Never use `--no-verify` or force-push to main/master without explicit request
- Prefer specific file staging over `git add -A`

## Code

- Edit existing files rather than creating new ones
- No backwards-compatibility shims, renamed `_unused` vars, or `// removed` comments
- No error handling for scenarios that can't happen
- No feature flags or abstractions for one-time use
- Trust internal code; only validate at system boundaries (user input, external APIs)

## Rules

See `~/.claude/rules/` for additional context-specific instructions.
